# Chess Timer - Track Two Players

Welcome to the Chess Timer project! This website provides a simple and intuitive chess timer that allows two players to track their time during a game. The timer is designed to be responsive and easy to use, whether you're playing a quick blitz game or a longer match.

## Features
- **Dual Timer**: Separate timers for both white and black players.
- **Time Control**: Set the initial time, increment, and method for time management.
- **Responsive Design**: Optimized for both desktop and mobile views.
- **Sound Notifications**: Alerts when switching turns to help keep track of the game.
- **Keyboard Support**: Use the spacebar to switch the clock between players.

## How to Use
1. Open the `index.html` file in your web browser or visit the live website.
2. Set the initial time for both players, choose the increment, and select the timing method.
3. Press the start button to begin the game. Use the spacebar or click on the timer to switch turns.
4. The timer will automatically switch between the players, tracking the time difference.

## Visit the Website
Check out the live version of the Chess Timer: [Chess Timer - Track Two Players](https://chessmoveexpert.com/chess-timer-track-two-players)

## Technologies Used
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling.
- **JavaScript** for timer functionality and event handling.
- **HTML5 Audio** for sound notifications.

